uk.ac.rdg.resc.edal.graphics.formats

Class JpegFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.rdg.resc.edal.graphics.formats.ImageFormat
      • uk.ac.rdg.resc.edal.graphics.formats.SimpleFormat
        • uk.ac.rdg.resc.edal.graphics.formats.JpegFormat

  • public class JpegFormat
extends SimpleFormat
    Writes JPEG images using the ImageIO class. Only one instance of this class will ever be created, so this class contains no member variables to ensure thread safety.
    Author:
    Jon Blower

        public void writeImage(List<BufferedImage> frames,
                       OutputStream out,
                       Integer frameRate)
                throws IOException
        Description copied from class: SimpleFormat
        Writes the given list of BufferedImages to the given OutputStream. If this ImageFormat doesn't support animations then the given list of frames should only contain one entry, otherwise an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
        Specified by:
        writeImage in class SimpleFormat
        Parameters:
        frames - List of BufferedImages to render into an image
        out - The OutputStream to which the image will be written
        frameRate - The frame rate to use if this is an animation.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there was an error writing to the output stream
